  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Manager (Construction)",
  "description": "<p></p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead and coordinate cross-functional teams of construction workers, subcontractors, and engineers to deliver projects that meet schedule, budget, and quality objectives</li><li>Develop and implement detailed project plans, schedules, and resource allocation strategies to maximize productivity and efficiency</li><li>Monitor project progress continuously, identify risks proactively, and execute corrective actions to maintain project timelines and standards</li><li>Ensure strict adherence to all applicable health, safety, environmental regulations, and company policies to maintain a safe work environment</li><li>Communicate effectively with clients, architects, and stakeholders by providing timely updates and resolving project-related concerns</li><li>Drive continuous improvement initiatives by evaluating and enhancing construction processes and procedures</li><li>Interpret and apply construction drawings, specifications, and technical documents to guide project execution</li></ul><p><strong>Job Requirements</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum 5 years of experience as a Site Manager in construction</li><li>Proven ability to deliver construction projects on time and within budget</li><li>Strong problem-solving, decision-making, and leadership skills demonstrated through managing the project</li><li>Comprehensive knowledge of construction techniques, building codes, and project management methodologies</li><li>Proficiency in reading and interpreting construction drawings, specifications, and technical documents</li><li>Effective communication and interpersonal skills to engage with diverse stakeholders</li><li>Relevant tertiary qualification in Construction Management, Civil Engineering, or a related field</li></ul>",
